    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-10-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/379.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Counselor of the Japanese
                            Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Third Assistant Secretary of
                            State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial Japanese Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Phillips</hi>: Some time ago I told you that my
                    Government would officially communicate to the Chinese Government their assent
                    to the prohibition of morphia and its instruments to China.</p>
                <p>I have now learned that the communication was made by our chargé d’affaires at
                    Peking to the Wauwupu on the 15th instant., The State Department have probably
                    already heard from your minister in China to the same effect. But I take
                    pleasure to let you know the above for the information of the department.</p>
                <p>Yours, very truly,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">K. Matsui.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
